headline.main: U. S. CASUALTIES SET AT 115,201 TO DATE; Army Places Its Losses at 85,039 While the Navy's Figure Is 30,162

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Sept. 30 -- American casualties including killed, wounded, missing and prisoners, have risen to approximately 115,000 during the war so far, it was revealed today.
